=== KEY OBSERVATION ===
- Same EPC (0x81fb91a8) and BADVADDR (0xc0000000) as prior session
  with VR1200v sysupgrade flashed
- This means our XR500v-specific DTS changes did NOT change the
  kernel's early boot path crashing point
- The crash is at offset 0x1f971a8 from kernel base 0x80020000
  → ~31MB into the kernel — likely in driver init or platform setup
- 0xc0000000 is MIPS KSEG2 — typically reserved for memory-mapped
  peripherals via TLB. Kernel is trying to access something that
  the EN751221 platform code expects but doesn't exist on XR500v
